main event: Two unidentified objects were detected on radar at the Los Angeles International Airport and Long Beach Municipal Tower.
interesting points: The objects were initially detected as two objects, then one object.
The objects were rectangular in shape and moved at a speed of approximately 3,000 mph.

The objects were detected at an altitude of 30,000 feet, moved at a range of approximately 10 miles, then approached the station to within 10 miles, stopped, and then proceeded at 220 knots before rapidly moving beyond the range of the radar.
The radar station lost high voltage and went off shortly after the sighting.
The report includes a determination that the sighting could have been a balloon, aircraft, astronomical object, or an unknown.
sighted object: two rectangular objects, then one rectangular object
location: Los Angeles International Airport and Long Beach, California
witnesses: civilian air operation specialists and tower operators
